Durban - Police have arrested one of the three suspectsÂ who shot a Cowie's Hill man outside his home in the early hours of Friday morning. According to KZN police, the man had just arrived at his Buckingham Place home when he came under attack by the armed men. "The victim sustained a gunshot wound to the chest after he was allegedly shot by one of the suspects," said Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane. He said the 55-year-old victim who was also in possession firearm, retaliated and shot at the suspects who then fled the scene on foot." The victim is recovering in hospital. Zwane said police found one of the suspects dead in the bush, while another suspect, aged 25, who was hiding in the bushes was also arrested. "The third suspect fled the scene." The arrested suspect will be charged for attempted robbery and attempted murder and will appear in the Pinetown Magistrate's Court soon. Daily News